    "description": {
      "value": "<em>You can fire your weapon and strike with it at the same time.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Grit class feature or Amateur Gunslinger feat, pistol-whip deed.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>Whenever you use your pistol-whip deed, you can fire a single bullet from your firearm at the same time that you strike a foe with the butt of your firearm. You must spend a total of 2 grit points to use the pistol-whip deed in this way, and must still succeed at a ranged touch attack against the target of your pistolwhip deed to hit. You cannot use the scatter weapon quality of a firearm when you use this feat.",
